## Known Issues & Gotchas

| Issue | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| ESO SecretStore NotReady | `mountPath: auth/kubernetes` (wrong path) | Use `mountPath: kubernetes` in ESO YAML |
| LDAP bind DN mismatch | Bootstrap LDIF uses different base DN than `LDAP_BASE_DN` | Keep both consistent |
| Jenkins pod readiness timeout | Vault Agent init container slow or Vault sealed | Check `kubectl exec -n vault vault-0 -- vault status` |
| Empty LDAP directory | Basic `--enable-ldap` deploys with no users; `bootstrap-basic-schema.ldif` not yet created | Use `deploy_ad` for OpenLDAP+AD-schema with pre-seeded users; or set `LDAP_LDIF_PATH` to a custom LDIF |
| Cert rotator image pull failure | `google/cloud-sdk:slim` unreachable | Set `JENKINS_CERT_ROTATOR_IMAGE` to accessible registry |

---

## Security Rules

Full OWASP-aligned rules are in `CLAUDE.md` → Security Notes. Key checklist:

**Shell / Injection (A03)**
- Always double-quote bash variable expansions: `"$var"` not `$var`.
- Never use `eval` with external input.
- Use `--` separator in CLI calls where arguments may contain hyphens.

**Least Privilege (A01)**
- New Vault policies: `read`-only unless `write` is explicitly required.
- New ServiceAccounts: namespace-scoped Role/RoleBinding, never `cluster-admin`.
- GitHub Actions workflows: `permissions: contents: read` as baseline.

**Cryptographic / TLS (A02)**
- `TRUST_ALL_CERTIFICATES` and `insecureSkipVerify: true` are dev-only — document it.
- Never add `--insecure` / `-k` to production-path scripts.
- Vault PKI leaf TTL ≤720h. Do not raise without justification.

**Secrets (A02)**
- Never commit secrets or credentials to git.
- Use `${PLACEHOLDER}` variables in all templates; store secrets in Vault.
- New sensitive CLI flags → register in `_args_have_sensitive_flag` in `system.sh`.
- `_run_command` probes sudo safely; never call `sudo` directly.
- Vault tokens via env vars or stdin — never in CLI arguments.

**Misconfiguration (A05)**
- New services must use their own namespace — never `default`.
- `set -euo pipefail` mandatory on all new bash scripts.
- Helm installs must pin chart versions — no `latest`.

**Supply Chain (A08)**
- GitHub Actions: pin to version tags (`@v4`), never `@main` or `@latest`.
- Container images in `*.yaml.tmpl`: pinned tags only, never `latest`.

**Existing protections — do not remove:**
- `_args_have_sensitive_flag` auto-disables trace for `--password`, `--token`, `--username`.
- Vault PKI auto-revokes old certs after rotation.

